The paper proposes a method for classifying the functionality of individual buildings using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) based on street view images and remote sensing images. This involves image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of CNNs also suggests that the paper may fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves training and evaluating CNNs, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Geographic information is utilized, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the geographic information systems (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves generating building classification maps, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
